CONDITIONS MODIFIED 9/30/22:  Defendant may also have contact with the minor nephew who resides with the defendant. Defendant may also have contact with new grandchild with anticipated birthdate in 11/22.   Defendant to have no unsupervised contact with any child under the age of 18, with the exception of his own minor daughter, his grandson and minor nephew.  
Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  If DNA sample has not been taken from the defendant, the Court orders sample to be taken;  and it may be expunged under 165.77(4) Wis. Statutes.  Defendant to have no contact with Victim A/Victim B listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney.  Defendant is not to be located at any school or daycares.  Defendant is prohibited from accessing any child exploitation material and any other sexually explicit material through the Internet or by any other means.  Defendant prohibited from contacting a minor over the internet or using a website to gather information about a minor. Defendant is prohibited from intentionally deleting any history from any computer or device that accesses the Internet. Defendant prohibited from using any application where the content automatically deletes upon the recipient opening the content.  Defendant not to leave the State of Wisconsin without prior authorization from the Court, with the exception of going to Florida for the doctor visits of his minor child where he is scheduled to leave on October 5, 2022 and return on 10/8/22.  Defendant to surrender their passport to the Waukesha Criminal Traffic Office (Room C226) by close of business on March 4, 2022.  Court will allow for attendance at parent/teacher conference at the school only.
